name: AIR JORDAN 1 RETRO HIGH OG 'PINE GREEN'
description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Pine Green’ presents a new modifictation on the silhouette’s classic ‘Black Toe’ design, first introduced in 1985. The leather high-top employs a black and white color scheme with Pine Green accents on the heel, outsole, and leather wings that wrap around the collar. Departing the original ‘Black Toe’ design, the traditional white finish on the toe box is tempered with Pine Green.

name: AIR JORDAN 3 RETRO 'TRUE BLUE' 2011
description: The 2011 edition of the Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘True Blue’ celebrates the 23rd anniversary of the classic silhouette. The release is mostly true to the original, highlighted by a tumbled white leather upper with True Blue accents and grey elephant-print overlays along the toe, heel and eyestay. A red Jumpman on the tongue is matched by a second Jumpman icon on the heel, in lieu of the OG Nike Air branding.

name: AIR JORDAN 4 RETRO OG 'WHITE CEMENT' 2016
description: The Air Jordan 4 Retro OG ‘White Cement’ returned to store shelves in 2016, featuring a design that’s true to the original 1989 release. The build makes use of a white leather upper, accented with speckled Cement Grey hits on the shoe’s structural wings, midsole and heel panel, the latter adorned with Nike Air branding. A red Jumpman logo on the woven Flight tongue tag offers a contrasting pop of color.

name: STEVEN HARRINGTON X AIR FORCE 1 LOW FLYLEATHER QS 'EARTH DAY'
description: A collaboration between Nike and psychedelic-pop illustrator Steven Harrington, the Steven Harrington x Air Force 1 Low Flyleather QS 'Earth Day' released as part of a three-shoe pack for Earth Day 2019. The shoe updates the Air Force 1 with a cartoon illustration on the lateral-side quarter panel that continues down onto the midsole, with a sytlized tree graphic on the medial heel. The heel Swoosh and translucent outsole are mismatched, with blue on the right shoe and green on the left shoe. The Flyleather construction up top is supported underfoot by a classic midsole housing Air cushioning.

name: BLAZER MID '77 VINTAGE 'LUCID GREEN'
description: In true rettro style, the Nike Blazer Mid ’77 Vintage ‘Lucid Green’ sports a vintage design that calls to mind its 1970s basketball origins. The mid-top features a white leather upper highlighted with hits of Lucid Green on the Swoosh and heel tab. Suede overlays in the predominant color fortify the toe and sidewalls, and the off-white midsole and exposed-foam tongue espouse an old-school aesthetic.

name: STAN SMITH OG 'TUMBLED LEATHER'
description: The Stan Smith OG 'Tumbled Leather' emerges with an OG colorway. The shoe's white leather upper takes on a tumbled application throughout, with the signature green accents on the tongue tag and heel. Perforated Three-Stripes and gold 'Stan Smith' branding appear on the side wall, with an off-white sole unit contributing to a vintage feel.

name: SUPERSTAR 'WHITE BLACK'
description: The Superstar 'Running White' emerges with a familiar black and white look, including a full-grain leather upper and serrated leather Three-Stripes. The shoe's signature shelltoe complements the look in white, while the tongue includes gold branding, matched by the quarter panel. Underfoot, a white cuspole gives way to a herringbone pattern for traction.

name: PHARRELL X NMD HUMAN RACE 'INSPIRATION PACK'
description: One of four colorways, the Pharrell x adidas NMD ‘Inspiration Pack’ brings Pharrell’s unique design touch to the NMD. This model’s vibrant upper features a Power Blue knit embroidered with Chinese characters on the vamp, supported by a pink lacing cage that provides a contrasting pop. The orange outsole adds to the colorful design while providing traction, and a tribal-inspired pattern on the collar finishes off the colorway.
